 from one of Italy’s greatest writers investigates deep questions about the nature of faith, rebellion, fate, and free will.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aitalian, translation, gospel, gospel of judas, 12 disciples, jesus, Christianity, judas, crucifixion, morality, fiction, la gloria, Giuseppe Berto, novel, philosophy, catholic.1 aConti, Gregory, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVettori, Alessandro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024z978311079131040uhttps://doi.org/10.36019/978197883960140uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781978839601423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781978839601/original  a978-3-11-079131-0  Rutgers University Press Complete eBook-Package 2024b2024  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles